Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was an intern, or a first-year\Ndoctor in training, I knew something was
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.08,0:00:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong with me. I had trouble sleeping,\NI had difficulty feeling joy, I was prone
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.90,0:00:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to crying at inopportune times. Even\Nworse, I had trouble connecting with
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.00,0:00:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,patients. I felt like I couldn't please\Nanyone, and I found myself susceptible to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.44,0:00:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,feelings of despair and panic. I'm a\Nphysician!  and if I do say so myself, a very
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.96,0:00:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,well trained one. Yet it took an intern\Nsupport group, the social worker that ran
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.34,0:00:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it, close friends and my then fiancee and\Nnow wife to convince me that I might
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.12,0:00:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,need help. Even if I couldn't acknowledge\Nit, they could see I was suffering from
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.43,0:00:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,depression. I wasn't alone! that's the\Ntopic of this week's healthcare triage.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.34,0:00:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,last month the study in JAMA reviewed all\Nthe literature on depression and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.35,0:00:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,depressive symptoms in resident\Nphysicians. They found more than 50
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.17,0:00:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,studies on the subject. Research shows\Nthat almost 30% of resident physician
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.90,0:01:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,suffer from either symptoms, or a\Ndiagnosis of depression. The numbers and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.07,0:01:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,how they compare to other professions\Nare almost beside the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.76,0:01:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Physicians are in a unique position of\Nneeding to care for others continuously,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.72,0:01:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that strain coupled with an inability\Nto help themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.54,0:01:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,leaves both patients and doctors at risk.\N Longitudinal studies or those that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.90,0:01:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,follow resident over the course of their\Ntraining, found that the rate of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.54,0:01:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,depressive issues in residents\Nincreased more than 15 percent within a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.75,0:01:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,year of beginning training. Worse, physicians\Nexist in a profession where admitting a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.87,0:01:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,problem carries with it a stigma that's\Nmore impactful than in some others.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.40,0:01:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A study published in 2008 surveyed\Nphysicians in Michigan, asking them about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.68,0:01:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,their work experiences as well as their\Ndepressive symptoms. More than 11 percent
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.06,0:01:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,reported moderate to severe depression\Nscores. About a quarter of them reported
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.62,0:01:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing a doctor whose professional\Nstanding had been hurt by being
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.81,0:01:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,depressed. Physicians with moderate to\Nsevere depression had a decrease in work
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.79,0:01:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,productivity and job satisfaction. They\Nwere also two to three times more likely
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.23,0:02:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to say that they were worried about or\Nhad difficulty getting mental health
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.15,0:02:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,care while the Americans with\NDisabilities Act passed in 1990 prohibits
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.46,0:02:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,employers from asking broad questions\Nabout illnesses when people apply for
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.12,0:02:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,jobs,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.93,0:02:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,state medical licensing board still ask\Nspecific questions about mental health.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.98,0:02:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of this physicians are much more\Nlikely to avoid treatment but also more
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.65,0:02:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,likely to self medicate. Sometimes that\Nmedication is potentially appropriate, as
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.15,0:02:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with anti-depressants. Often it is not. A\N2012 study in JAMA surgery found that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.40,0:02:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,more than 15% of the members of the\NAmerican College of Surgeons had a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.71,0:02:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,scoreless screening tests consistent\Nwith alcohol abuse or dependence. Among
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.66,0:02:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,female surgeons the prevalence was more\Nthan 25%. Those who were depressed were
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.12,0:02:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,significantly more likely to abuse or be\Ndependent on alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.53,0:02:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,doctors have much easier access to drugs\Nthan others as well. Because of this they
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.06,0:02:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,are more likely to misuse prescription\Ndrugs than the general population.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.84,0:03:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Anesthesiologist have access to even\Nmore drugs than other physicians and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.98,0:03:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,their problems are even more common. A 2005\Nstudy of anesthesia residency training
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.81,0:03:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,programs, found the eighty percent of\Nthem reported experiences with impaired
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.20,0:03:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,residence and almost 20% had experiences\Nwith at least one abuse related death of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.91,0:03:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,a doctrine training. Unfortunately\Ndepression and substance abuse can lead
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.40,0:03:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to further problems including suicide\Nmore than 6 percent of surgeons report
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.35,0:03:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,suicidal ideation in the last year you don't \N**______** one-quarter of then sought any kind of mental
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.41,0:03:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,health treatment. Most who did not fear \Nthe doing so would affect their ability
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.81,0:03:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to obtain a license., even though they\Nwere worried about killing themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.09,0:03:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is even worse among medical\Ntrainees. About 6 percent of them
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.03,0:03:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,reported thinking about suicide in the\Nlast two weeks. Those with a history of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.62,0:03:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,depression were almost four times as\Nlikely to report recent suicidal
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.44,0:03:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,thoughts as those without. Too many\Ndoctors act on suicidal impulses as well
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.85,0:03:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it's estimated that about 400 physicians\Ncommit suicide each year that's about
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.90,0:04:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,three times as many doctors as were in\Nmy medical school class at the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.43,0:04:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,University of Pennsylvania. Meta-analyses\Nestimate the rate of suicide among male
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.09,0:04:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,physicians is a hundred and forty\Npercent that of the general population.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.28,0:04:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,among female physicians it's almost two\Nhundred and thirty percent. What makes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.40,0:04:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,this important to discuss is not the\Nprevalence of depression in physicians
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.00,0:04:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and trainees, although it's clearly too\Nhigh, it's not whether physicians have
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.59,0:04:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the highest suicide rate of any\Nprofessional, although many people argue
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.77,0:04:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that they do. The critical issue here is\Nthat too many positions especially
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.30,0:04:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,trainees suffer in silence, afraid to ask\Nfor help for fear that they will be
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.25,0:04:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,punished professionally if not\Npersonally. I've always been very open
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.83,0:04:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,about my time in residency,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.81,0:04:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and how depression someone robbed me of a few\Nyears of my life. When I look back, I
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.82,0:04:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,think the constant pressure to help\Nothers coupled with frequent feelings of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.22,0:04:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,helplessness wait on me, a lack of sleep\Nand being away from family and friends
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.69,0:04:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,left me vulnerable. Seeing children I've\Nbonded with and cared for deeply suffer
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.08,0:05:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and die was often more than I could bear.\NAnd I think some part of me whether it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.12,0:05:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,be physical or behavioral is also\Npredisposed to anxiety and depression. But
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.58,0:05:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm lucky, thanks to the support of those\Nwho love me as well as two excellent
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.39,0:05:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,therapist I'm no longer depressed. I\Nremain vigilant, however, against a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.94,0:05:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,recurrence. It's important for me and for\Nall physicians to stay on top of their
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.61,0:05:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,mental health and not wait for a crisis to\Nact. I've also felt fortunate to be in a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.79,0:05:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,specialty: pediatrics and a focused\Nresearch, where I didn't fear being found
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.64,0:05:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,out. many colleagues still **____** when I\Ntalked openly about therapy, or how I plan
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.63,0:05:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to go for the rest of my life. I'm sure\Nthey'll find this episode concerning as
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.67,0:05:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,well. But we can't not talk about this.\NToo many of us are suffering and if they
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.23,0:05:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,can't get help from others, they may try\Nand fail to help themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.80,0:05:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Suicide is always a tragedy. A physician\Ncommitting suicide is a travesty.
